Images in circulation pic.twitter.com/U2TniaaXru — GTP Gauteng Traffic Police (@GTP_Traffstats) February 17, 2023  JMPD spokesperson Xolani Fihla has advised motorists to exercise caution. “There is a tanker explosion on the N1 north, between Malibongwe and William Nicol. All lanes on the N1 north have been blocked to traffic. Motorists have been advised to exercise extreme caution and expect heavy delays. Motorists on the N1 north are being diverted at Malibongwe. Emergency services are en route. Currently, there are no causalities confirmed. The cause is not yet determined.” On arrival on scene, the tanker carrying an unconfirmed substance had exploded and was engulfed in flames. One person was treated for moderate injuries and taken by Emer-G-Med ambulance to a nearby hospital for further care. https://t.co/SrHg1LJ89g @EMER_G_MED #TankerExplosion https://t.co/EkJ2nnC8XC — Arrive Alive (@_ArriveAlive) February 17, 2023 